<?php
$str = "Hello World";

echo "<h2>String Manipulation</h2>";

echo "Original String: " . $str . "<br>";

echo "Length of String: " . strlen($str) . "<br>";

echo "Reverse String: " . strrev($str) . "<br>";

echo "Substring: " . substr($str, 0, 5) . "<br>";
?>





Code explanation
String variable
$str = "Hello World";
Stores the string in a variable.
Length
strlen($str)
Returns the number of characters.
Reverse
strrev($str)
Reverses the string.
Substring
substr($str, 0, 5)
Takes part of the string.
•	0 = starting position 
•	5 = number of characters 
